FBIS4-43974 "drweu121_o_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-121 Daily Report 22 Jun 1994 CYPRUS UN's Clark Arrives for Talks With Both Communities UN's Clark Arrives for Talks With Both Communities NC2206171794 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network in Greek 1500 GMT 22 Jun 94 NC2206171794 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network Greek BFN [Text] Joe Clark, the UN secretary general's special representative in Cyprus, arrived this afternoon and will meet President Glavkos Kliridhis tonight. In a statement after his arrival, Clark said he wants to discuss with the leaders of the two communities the current state of the confidence-building measures and other fundamental issues. Clark was answering a question on the contents of his mission, given that he is not carrying any letters from UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali.
